<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Measure_representation_arm
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm">
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Property_value_representation  
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Property_value_representation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Property_value_representation">
A <b>Property_value_representation</b> is a type of <b>Representation</b> that represents one or more quantity values.
<note>The present version of this application module does not enable to represent whether the values have been imposed or were derived or measured.
It is expected that a future version will add this capability.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Property_value_representation  Attribute: SELF\Representation.context_of_items 
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Property_value_representation.context_of_items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Property_value_representation.context_of_items">
the <b>Numerical_representation_context</b> in which the value is represented.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Measure_item  
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item">
A <b>Measure_item</b> is a type of <b>Representation_item</b> that conveys the value of a quantity. Only specializations of this entity can be instantiated.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Measure_item  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item.wr:WR1">
an instance of this entity shall be an item of at least a <b>Property_value_representation</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Numerical_item_with_global_unit  
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_global_unit"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_global_unit">
A <b>Numerical_item_with_global_unit</b> is a type of <b>Measure_item</b> where the value is expressed with respect to a unit provided as a global information associated with the representation context.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Numerical_item_with_global_unit  Attribute: value_component 
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_global_unit.value_component"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_global_unit.value_component">
the value of the quantity. The type of this value shall be consistent with exactly one of the units globally assigned within the Numerical_representation_context.
<example>
If the type of the value is mass_value, there shall be exactly one mass_unit in the units of the Numerical_representation_context.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Numerical_item_with_global_unit  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_global_unit.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_global_unit.wr:WR1">
an instance of this entity shall be an item of at least a <b>Property_value_representation</b> for which global units are specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Measure_representation_arm  Entity: Numerical_item_with_unit  
   <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_unit"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_unit">
A <b>Numerical_item_with_unit</b> is a type of <b>Measure_item</b> that is also a <b>Value_with_unit</b>.
The quantity value is therefore provided with its own unit.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
